name: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellee v. Larry RUSH, Appellant

parties: COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellee v. Larry RUSH, Appellant.

opinions.text:
ORDER
PER CURIAM.
AND NOW, this 26th day of June, 2008, the “Motion to Quash Frivolous Appeal Filed by No-Good-For-Nothing Court Appointed Lawyer ... on Behalf of the Commonwealth” is GRANTED, and the Commonwealth’s Motion for Appointment of Counsel and Remand is DENIED.
opinions.author: PER CURIAM.

attorneys: David S. Rudenstein, Esq., for Larry Rush.
Catherine Marshall, Esq., Philadelphia, for Commonwealth.
Robert A. Graci, Esq., Harrisburg, for Office of Attorney General.
casebody.head_matter:
950 A.2d 979
COMMONWEALTH of Pennsylvania, Appellee v. Larry RUSH, Appellant.

Supreme Court of Pennsylvania.
June 26, 2008.
David S. Rudenstein, Esq., for Larry Rush.
Catherine Marshall, Esq., Philadelphia, for Commonwealth.
Robert A. Graci, Esq., Harrisburg, for Office of Attorney General.
